        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:19PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1218 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Oreana, or 38 miles south of Nampa, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Oreana around 1230 PM MDT.
Big Foot Butte around 1250 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
